yers parents ralph f and alice in  and was named after their hometown of johnsonville wis stayer became president in  and expanded the company by selling johnsonvilles products outside wisconsin about the talk stayer was interviewed by dr erik ugland associate dean for graduate studies and research and associate professor in marquettes j william and mary diederich college of communication during a circles networking event stayer talked about his recipe for success as president of johnsonville which includes encouraging employees to ask questions and take ownership of key situations about the series circles this lecture was part of circles an innovative business networking program that connects marquette alumni with people doing business in fields such as health care finance journalism and real estate learn more marquette circles johnsonville sausage link   embed bookmark this page email link to a friend your name  your email address  friend name  friend email address  message antispam check  enter the two words above separated by a space include any hyphens cant identify the words click here for another pair required fields   the difference network offers access to key thought leaders on and off campus new video content is added regularly get notified of new content   scott vandersanden rethinking the possible iphones apps wifi video scott vandersanden discussed them all — and how att has pivoted to focus on these mobile broadband capabilities — in the past five years more business videos explore the difference network human interest captured and released the story of james foley business business models building brands and ethics business the future of banking exclusive from the business journals power breakfast human interest marquette universitys  commencement address faith dorothy day a saint for todays world business mu to silicon valley changing health care one startup at a time human interest the wet solar system polar ice on the earth and moon water on mars 